msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:39
msgid ""
"In order to use the audio output of the controller, select the device "
":guilabel:`Traktor Kontrol S4 MK3`. :guilabel:`Channels 1 - 2` should be set"
" as :guilabel:`Main` and :guilabel:`Channels 3 - 4` should be set as "
":guilabel:`Headphones`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:42
msgid "Using the software mixer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:44
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use certain outputs of the device, you can enable the "
"mapping of the mixer knob to the Mixxx internal mixer. Head over to the "
":ref:`settings` to enable these optional mappings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:46
msgid ""
"The mixer knobs are physically linked to the S4 embedded mixer. This means "
"that there is no way to prevent these buttons to adjust gains of the output,"
" and will lead to unexpected volume mixing if the Mixxx mixer is used while "
"also using S4 outputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:50
msgid "Known bugs and limitation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:53
msgid "Audio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:55
msgid ""
"During the development phase, it appears that using other Sound API than "
"`ALSA` would lead the Master VU meter not to work. Furthermore, audio output"
" power would be half as loud as it should be, which can be a problem if you "
"are also using other software, since you audio setting will suddenly become "
"twice as loud. It remains unclear whether or not this was a common issue or "
"if this was specific to the used setup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:60
msgid "Screens"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:62
msgid ""
"Currently, Mixxx doesn't support controller screen rendering. However, "
"because the screens are technically a different device, it is safe to "
"interact with them outside of Mixxx while the device is being used by Mixxx."
" This can be particularly handy if you want to display some images or text, "
"or even dynamic information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:68
msgid "Motors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:70
msgid ""
"Haptic feedback (know as Haptic Drive (TM)) are partially implemented. "
"Supported features include jogwheel tensions and turntable mode but these "
"features remains in beta and may sometime have unexpected behaviours. Since "
"there is no guarantee on the long term effect to the controller of how Mixxx"
" implements these features, they are disabled by default. You can enable "
"them by setting `UseMotors` to `true` in :ref:`settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:76
msgid "Mapping Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:81
msgid "Jogwheel modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:83
msgid ""
"Jogwheel can be used to control various things, depending of the mode they "
"are in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:85
msgid ""
"**Vinyl mode** (*default*): The jogwheel platter can be used for scratch. "
"The jogwheel crown can be used to jog up or down the playback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:86
msgid ""
"**Jog mode**: The wheel platter and crown can be used to jog up or down the "
"playback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:87
msgid ""
"**Turntable mode**: The wheel behaves as a 33.3 RPM turntable. If the "
"platter or crown are slowed down or speeded up, then it will scratch down or"
" up the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:89
msgid ""
"Because this mode relies on Mixxx's scratch mode, if the track has been "
"pitched up, the keylock will be ignored!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:91
msgid ""
"This mode is only available if the motor features are enabled. See "
":ref:`use-motors` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:93
msgid ""
"**Loop in**: The wheel behaves similarly to CDJ. If the platter or crown are"
" turned, it will move back or forth the start of the loop. Additionally, if "
"the loop encoder is used, it will move the all loop back or forth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/native_instruments_traktor_kontrol_s4_mk3.rst:94
msgid ""
"**Loop out**: Like for the **loop in** mode, but with the exit position of "
"the loop. If the platter or crown are turned, it will move back or forth the"
" end of the loop. Additionally, if the loop encoder is used in the same way "
"than **Loop in** mode."
msgstr ""

